When I call the register method more than once, the logs are full of this kind of message

issue.body:
### What happened?

I have a test that visits multiple websites protected with basic authentication, each having different credentials. I am using RemoteWebDriver, so I need to use addDriverAugmentation, to be able to use the register method from HasAuthentication interface. When I call the register method more than once, the logs are full of this kind of message
`DevToolsException: {"id":14,"error":{"code":-32602,"message":"Invalid InterceptionId."}`
Adding basic authentication works, the protected websites are reached but the logs are practically unreadable because of the many DevToolsExceptions

### How can we reproduce the issue?

```shell
driver = new Augmenter().augment(driver);
DevTools devTools = ((HasDevTools) driver).getDevTools();
devTools.createSession();

Augmenter augmenter = new Augmenter();
driver = augmenter
         .addDriverAugmentation("chrome",
             HasAuthentication.class,
             caps, exec) -> (whenThisMatches, useTheseCredentials) ->
                 devTools.getDomains()
                     .network()
                     .addAuthHandler(whenThisMatches, useTheseCredentials))
         .augment(driver);

Predicate<URI> mallUri = uri -> uri.getHost().contains("the-internet.herokuapp.com");
((HasAuthentication) driver).register(mallUri, UsernameAndPassword.of("admin", "admin"));

Predicate<URI> siosUri = uri -> uri.getHost().contains("authenticationtest.com");
((HasAuthentication) driver).register(siosUri, UsernameAndPassword.of("user", "pass"));

driver.get("https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/basic_auth");
Thread.sleep(10000);

driver.get("https://authenticationtest.com/HTTPAuth/");
Thread.sleep(10000);
```
